      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "Rise of the zero-degree level up to 3400 m. <br/> <br/> The early morning will see favourable conditions, but the danger of wet and gliding avalanches will increase later. <br/> As a consequence of warming during the day and solar radiation the avalanche prone locations will become more prevalent from the late morning. These conditions will cause a rapid weakening of the snowpack in particular on steep sunny slopes. Medium-sized natural avalanches are possible here. Increase in danger of moist and wet snow slides in particular in steep rocky terrain. <br/> <br/> Backcountry tours and off-piste skiing should be started and concluded very early. <br/> <br/> Especially on very steep northwest, north and northeast facing slopes avalanches can be triggered in the weakly bonded old snow. This applies in particular in case of a large load.",
        "highlights": "The danger of moist and wet avalanches will already increase in the late morning."
