      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The surface of the snowpack will freeze to form a strong crust only at high altitudes and will soften earlier than the day before. <br/> <br/> Especially steep shady slopes high altitudes: Individual weak layers exist in the centre of the snowpack. <br/> <br/> At elevated altitudes snow depths vary greatly, depending on the infuence of the wind. <br/> In general, snow conditions in many regions are still good and are in line with or above the seasonal average. At low altitude and on sunny slopes the snowpack will soften quickly."
